    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9977</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-20">August 20,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Gaucheron of the French Embassy telephoned this morning and said that he
                    wished to supplement the information contained in the informal memorandum which
                    he gave me on August 19 by stating that the French Government would be prepared,
                    if such action were needed to make effective the British proposal, to furnish a
                    small detachment for use also in the International Settlement at Shanghai.<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d503fn50">This information was transmitted to the British
                        Ambassador on August 21 in a note from the Under Secretary of State
                        (793.94/9642).</note>
                </p>
                <p>I thanked Mr. Gaucheron for his courtesy in communicating this information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
